value.value: A soft tissue tumor of uncertain lineage characterized by the presence of neoplastic spindle-shaped to round cells in a fibromyxoid stroma. Metaplastic bone formation may or may not be present.

label.value: malignant vaginal mixed epithelial and mesenchymal neoplasm

value.value: A malignant neoplasm that arises from the vagina and is characterized by the presence of an epithelial and a mesenchymal component. This category includes adenosarcoma, carcinosarcoma, and malignant mixed tumor resembling synovial sarcoma.
A injury that involves the vertebral column.
An elevated concentration of lipoproteins.
A disease that has its basis in the disruption of carbohydrate metabolic process.
A disease that has its basis in the disruption of porphyrin-containing compound metabolic process.
A disease that has its basis in the disruption of purine nucleobase metabolic process.
A group of genetic disorders that result from the inability to produce or use an enzyme required to oxidize fatty acids, resulting in an inability to generate energy from fatty acid sources.
A disease that has its basis in the disruption of valine metabolic process.
A disease that has its basis in the disruption of cellular amino acid metabolic process.
Any disease caused by infection with organisms of the genus Bordetella.
A disease that has its basis in the disruption of pyrimidine nucleobase metabolic process.

label.value: inborn disorder of aspartate family metabolism

value.value: An inherited metabolic disease that is has its basis in the disruption of aspartate family amino acid metabolic process.

Porphyria is a group of diseases in which substances called porphyrins build up, negatively affecting the skin or nervous system. Most types are inherited, but porphyria cutanea tarda may also be due to increased iron in the liver, hepatitis C, alcohol, or HIV/AIDS.
An instance of auditory system disease that is caused by an inherited modification of the individual's genome.
An inherited metabolic disease that is has its basis in the disruption of glutathione metabolic process.
Autosomal recessive form of ocular albinism (disease).
Autosomal dominant form of oculocutaneous albinism.
A malignant germ cell tumor that affects the peritoneum.
A benign, well circumscribed soft tissue neoplasm characterized by the presence of spindle shaped myofibroblasts and mast cells in a collagenous stroma.
A malignant neoplasm arising from the great vessels.
A carcinoma that is not confined to the epithelium, and has spread to the surrounding stroma.
A invasive carcinoma that involves the urothelium.

OBSOLETE. A proliferation of the endometrial cells resulting in glandular enlargement and budding. The proliferation may or may not be associated with atypia of the endometrial cells. When the hyperplastic changes are excessive, there is formation of complex epithelial structures (complex endometrial hyperplasia).
An myocarditis caused by infection with Corynebacterium diphtheriae.
Acute form of kidney papillary necrosis.
Acute form of epiglottitis.

label.value: metastatic malignant neoplasm in the colon

value.value: The spread of a malignant neoplasm to the colon. This may be from a primary large intestine malignant neoplasm, or from a malignant neoplasm at a distant site.

label.value: metastasis from malignant tumor of colon

value.value: Tuberculosis disease caused by Mycobacterium tuberculosis isolate that is resistant to one or more of the antitubercular medications.

label.value: bacterial meningitis caused by gram-negative bacteria
pneumonia caused by gram negative bacteria

value.value: An pneumonia caused by infection with Staphylococcus aureus.

Systemic candidiasis occurs when Candida yeast enters the bloodstream and may spread (becoming disseminated candidiasis) to other organs, including the central nervous system, kidneys, liver, bones, muscles, joints, spleen, or eyes.
An endocarditis (disease) caused by infection with Fungi.
An inflammation of the endometrium and the myometrium.
The inflammation of one or more joints caused by any infectious pathogen within the joint space. Symptoms include pain, stiffness, and decreased range of motion in the affected joint.
Stage 0 includes: (Tis, N0, M0). Tis: Carcinoma in situ. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 6th ed.) - 2003
Infections with true tapeworms of the helminth subclass Cestoda.

A constitution or condition of the body which makes the tissues react in special ways to certain extrinsic stimuli and thus tends to make the individual more than usually susceptible to certain diseases.
